reviews.text: We grabbed an early lunch there and it was incredible!  The fried calamari appetizer was fantastic ‚Äì crispy on the outside and perfectly tender inside. The deep dish took about 45 minutes, but absolutely worth the wait. The toppings were amazing, and the dough was the best I've ever had in a deep dish.  The service was also top-notch, and the restaurant itself is very nicely decorated. We'll definitely be back if we're ever in the area again!

I'm glad we found this place. The Baked Penne was absolutely amazing.
We can't wait to come back and try their pizza.

Well.. I‚Äôd like to think I‚Äôve tried a decent amount of pizza in my time. This pizza upon first bite seemed tasty. Then I realized how awful the crust was, it was simply un-chewable. Both my son and I gave up and just ate the fries. Not for me. Included is a pic of my dear dog trying to muscle down this za. She struggled.

Ordered a slice of pizza, ravioli, and soup of the day.

The soup was like a minestrone. Usually I don't like a minestrone. This soup was good. Hearty comfort food. I would order it again.

Ravioli was good. Had a bit of cinnamon in it which was almost a turn off. Good quality pasta dish. Definitely would order it again.

Pizza slice was a disgrace. Old! Dried out! Not edible food. Really disgusting. Had gas station pizza that was better. Very surprised with the freshness of the other 2 dishes that I received something so bad. It had to be several hours old under a heat lamp. üò´

Sometimes it's more than just pizza!!!
We had a family member who got sick one hot afternoon in their parking lot (we were 4 hours from home traveling for a basketball tournament).  The kindness and concern for our loved one was something that will NEVER be forgotten.  The compassionate woman working made my young daughter a special drink to help get her back up and feeling better.  So thank you for you random act of kindness - WE WILL PAY IT FORWARD :)

2/27/25: Ordered a pizza the other night, another Win! Brasi's is just great Pizza! Ordered them a ton of times since the last post, Pizza and Dinners. 6/1/2024: Favorite Go To Pizza and So Much More! Pizza hands down: Great! BUT, they have so many other great meals: add a side of Fettuccine Alfredo for only $5 bucks(So F'n Good, Phenomenal!), Brasi's Chicken: OH MY!, Great Ranch Dressing: If you know you know! Canoli's & More! Great Wings too!

Original Post:
The more we eat Brasi's the more we love Brasi's. Dan's Pizza was always a go-to favorite but they never have delivery after 715/730pm, and they close so early. Sucks. They say they can't find staff but how come every other pizza place can?  So had to start looking around for other places and talking to others in the area they feel the same. Brasi's so good, so good! Favorites: Fettuccine Alfredo, Lasagna, Pizza, chicken vesuvio. Canoli's are good too. If you want good quality, great tasting like you're at a restaurant then get Brasi's. You will not be disappointed. And the staff and the owner have been fantastic!

detailedReviews.author: Leesa
detailedReviews.text: We've been going to Brasi's about once a week since we moved to Glen Ellyn almost a year ago. The food is fantastic with the freshest ingredients and home made sauces. The specials are to die for, try the salmon, even if it's not on special that day they will make it for you. The family that owns the place is always there to welcome you and make you feel special and  at home.

detailedReviews.author: Nooch
detailedReviews.text:
A wonderful Italian pizzeria and eatery. The owner is extremely passionate about serving good quality and authentic Italian food.

My wife brought me there for a meal with her work friends. I soon found out who the owner is, and was ecstatic.  I've known this food for over 40 years, and never been disappointed.

It's in the sauce, the ingredients, and the prep, and most important, the love üôÇ

The restaurant may be new, but there is over 40 years of personal experience owning and running a pizzeria. Their sauce, well... Awesome!

I have been enjoying the pizza from the owner since I was a child, back in the Bensenville days, when they first opened a small little carryout Pizza joint.

I'm a fan of pepperoni, peppers, and onions. With a salad on the side.  The eggplant Parmesan, very good; good pasta with great sauce.

Hope this helps, and hope you enjoy! üôÇ I certainly did.

detailedReviews.author: Brittany Gyoerkoes
detailedReviews.text: Delicious pizza and always the friendliest service! Our favorite neighborhood pizza place!

detailedReviews.author: Thomas Ruiz
detailedReviews.text:
First time trying and will definitely be our new go to for pizza as well as Italian food!  The deep dish pizza is better than the big chains and the portion sizes are very generous.

Also, shout out to whoever the front of house waitress was for handling a disruptive customer who was upset for waiting an extra few minutes for their pizza to come out even though you could clearly tell the restaurant is a little short staffed. As someone who used to work as a host at a restaurant, kudos to you for keeping your calm and doing your best. Those type of entitled people are not worth your business any way and they can go to McDonald's if they want food when they say they want it.

detailedReviews.author: Nicole Riopelle
detailedReviews.text: Great food. Our server was a rockstar. Thank you.
